name.text: Fill ANOVA table for 2-year tomato data

questiontext.text:
An experiment was conducted for two years to investigate the effect three factors of light, heat and variety, each at two levels, on the yields of tomatoes.

Here is an incomplete analysis of variance (ANOVA) table for the tomato data for the \(2\) years together.

Complete the ANOVA table.

Give the values to \(1\) decimal place.

generalfeedback.text:
The complete ANOVA table is shown below.

There are a few key points to remember:

  • The residual is the "left over" after taking into account the variables. So the residual Df and sum of squares is the difference between the total values and the sum of the variables values.
  • The mean sum of squares is simply the sum of squares per Df.
  • The F value is the ratio of the mean sum of squares and the residual sum of squares. It allows us to compare the variability explained by a variable compared to the unexplained (residual) variability.
